FzGxEUPxPa81H4sfg1J27i_CaH0IaafvSoZsfC-SHDvDvtyLUcgzzNMb628vJTQAzQJEMQHFnnVYZHuGAuzdFk2BWV2Bd8_QriFFMJ9Lwq10MDQzjfvGYODSQY35zRBnJvWeuK3DRM3o-LkU6ZDN4JSOiLRY7xPsgS59-djiLNchql_3r6F0n8y9LaUEyXElkt4OtTuUj3-S_v_pc3WHmVW4GbDK9qiBr3qtVwwzioqKQDzaxVAZPoyg8w8DxFmLyPFViNxBJHraJaC20zC-OfNs8p4pJMdDJndraMtUy8rKjWUNFT0_DgcfZ7DIQgOKoWDvtli7g0JmkjJCWsu58YoFjyke5cNisGcX0sN1yYfAFqRC-oPa4Jq7H7Pd7hACev_qIGk91pxHt-bHCES0TglXeRr2wqonRnNVr7IJ3Fm5EWO0iVu4exwheCKgK_p6decV-fdSYDepLh08cDwHGQxlWPBu4KMdmf_yN-e-aPoXdLe70RksWKqfuAuW6AFkn\",\"summary\":[{\"type\":\"summary_text\",\"text\":\"**Clarifying resource resolution**\\n\\nI need to understand how to use `Class#getResource(String)`. If the string doesn't have a leading slash, it resolves relative to `org/javamoney/moneta/internal/loader`. I can utilize `/class-loader-resource.txt` to search from the root. But I see that `ClassLoader#getResource` with a leading slash requires the resource name without one. Otherwise, it usually returns null, which is something I need to keep in mind when implementing this.\"},{\"type\":\"summary_text\",\"text\":\"**Inspecting resource loading**\\n\\nI'm focused on ensuring that the DefaultLoaderService is instantiated correctly to make sure LoaderConfigurator.load is executed effectively. However, I need to think about direct internal imports being public and how tests should be set up outside the library package. It's crucial that the DefaultLoaderService constructor initializes and loads local resources properly. I’ll verify aspects such as resource registration, retrieval policies, and whether the data has content. Plus, I must ensure input streams are closed!\"}]}"}, {"type": "toolCall", "id": "call_rcRrm3miV3lCICKSsv606nxT|fc_0dfeda377f850c540169f15489849c819ca705c091d39c0fcc", "name": "read", "arguments": {"path": "/home/vjovanov/c/forge5/metadata-forge/local_repositories/source_context/org.javamoney.moneta/moneta-core/1.3/main/extracted/org/javamoney/moneta/internal/loader/LoadableResource.java", "li